title: LEARNING BAYESIAN MODELS WITH R
description: Author: Dr. Hari M. Koduvely Publication Date: October 28, 2015 Publisher: Packt Publishing - ebooks Account ISBN-10: 178398760X ISBN-13: 978-1783987603 Pages: 168 pages Format: pdf Size: 1.3M --- This book is for statisticians, analysts, and data scientists who want to build a Bayes-based system with R and implement it in their day-to-day models and projects. It is mainly intended for Data Scientists and Software Engineers who are involved in the development of Advanced Analytics applications. To understand this book, it would be useful if you have basic knowledge of probability theory and analytics and some familiarity with the programming language R. --- http://dlfeb.com/book/learning-bayesian-models-with-r/
